                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/198</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Caffery</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-02">October 2,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I had a visit this afternoon from Señor Espil, the Argentine Ambassador, who came
                    to talk to me about the treaty conversations. He and I agreed that the best
                    first step on his part would be to give us a memorandum setting out the general
                    ideas of the Argentine Government in pertinent connection. He said that he would
                    hand it to me on Thursday next.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J[<hi rend="smallcaps">efferson</hi>] C[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >affery</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
